Message 3607 of 4024
See attached.
The original language for Cabo was drafted by your lawyer, approved by you and sent to us on July 1st. This was your original proposal. We did not
write this language, it came from you.
We approved the Cabo language drafted and approved by you on July 3. Cabo was not an issue.
All issues were agreed middle of last week July 3rd.
We asked to reschedule Rosen on July 3rd.
Your lawyer sent back revised language for Cabo on Friday July 5. Your lawyer was aware everyone was out for the holiday weekend. She had receipt
of out of office replies stating as such with return on Monday. This was only issue remaining but there was no indication to cancel Rosen on your
side, as we requested. You continued to reserve right to have Rosen decide this issue.
We responded Monday July 8 am, once everyone was back in the office. Again we asked to reschedule Rosen if this was one remaining issue. Your side
did not agree to do so.
This has cost you thousands.
All documented.
Sent:07/11/2024 at 07:09 PM
From:Christine Moyer
To:Robert Moyer (First Viewed: 07/11/2024 at 07:09 PM)
Subject:Original temp orders sent by your lawyer and approved by you
